#: ../../docs/classes/class_collisionshape2d.rst:19
msgid ""
"Editor facility for creating and editing collision shapes in 2D space. "
"You can use this node to represent all sorts of collision shapes, for "
"example, add this to an :ref:`Area2D <class_Area2D>` to give it a "
"detection shape, or add it to a :ref:`PhysicsBody2D "
"<class_PhysicsBody2D>` to create a solid object. **IMPORTANT**: this is "
"an Editor-only helper to create shapes, use "
":ref:`CollisionObject2D.shape_owner_get_shape "
"<class_CollisionObject2D_method_shape_owner_get_shape>` to get the actual"
" shape."
msgstr ""

